HEADWORD: Aubade
<hw>Au`bade"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>aube</ets> the dawn, fr. L. <ets>albus</ets> white.]</ety> <def>An
open air concert in the morning, as distinguished from an evening
serenade; also, a pianoforte composition suggestive of morning.</def>
<rj><au>Grove.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The crowing cock . . .⟦br⟧
Sang his <qex>aubade</qex> with lusty voice and clear.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aubaine</ent>⟦br⟧
